Package org.opengis.wrapper.netcdf

Class NetcdfParameter<T>

  • Object
    • NetcdfIdentifiedObject
      • NetcdfParameter<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of parameter value.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Cloneable, Identifier, GeneralParameterDescriptor, GeneralParameterValue, ParameterDescriptor<T>, ParameterValue<T>, IdentifiedObject, ReferenceIdentifier
    public class NetcdfParameter<T>
extends NetcdfIdentifiedObject
implements ParameterValue<T>, ParameterDescriptor<T>, Cloneable
    A ParameterValue implementation backed by a netCDF Parameter object. The netCDF Parameter class is both a parameter value and its own descriptor. Consequently this adapter implements both the ParameterValue and ParameterDescriptor interfaces.

    NetCDF Parameter instances can store the following types:

    Allowed parameter types
    Value type Getter method Setter method
    String stringValue() setValue(Object)
    double doubleValue() setValue(double)
    double[] doubleValueList() setValue(Object)
    All other fooValue() methods delegate to one of the above-cited getter methods and convert the result.
    Since:
    3.1
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

    • Constructor Detail

      • NetcdfParameter

        protected NetcdfParameter​(Parameter parameter,
                          Collection<GenericName> aliases)
        Creates a new wrapper for the given netCDF parameter. The value class will be inferred from the given parameter.

        Type safety:
        This constructor can not have public access because we can not guarantee that the <T> parameterized type is consistent with the given netCDF parameter object, since the netCDF class is not parameterized. Use the one of the create methods instead.

        Parameters:
        parameter - the parameter to wrap.
        aliases - an immutable collection of aliases (typically the OGC and EPSG names), or null or an empty collection if none. This collection is not cloned.
